ngers vs. New York Islanders]]\n|Games 1, 4\n|[[Gary Thorne]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|''[[Al Morganti]]''\n|-\n|[[1993\u201394 Dallas Stars season|Dallas]] vs. [[1993\u201394 St. Louis Blues season|St. Louis]]\n|Games 1, 4<ref>{{YouTube|title=Dallas Stars vs St. Louis Blues Game 4 1994 Playoffs ABC introduction |id=6o_UQEAIB90}}</ref>\n|[[Tom Mees]]\n|[[Darren Pang]] (Game 1)<br>[[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]] (Game 4)\n|''[[Bob Neumeier]]'' (Game 1)\n|-\n|[[1994 Stanley Cup playoffs|Conference semifinals]]\n|[[1993\u201394 New Jersey Devils season|New Jersey]] vs. [[1993\u201394 Boston Bruins season|Boston]]\n|Game 1\n|[[Gary Thorne]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|''[[Al Morganti]]''\n|}\n\n===The NHL returns to ABC (1999\u20132004)===\nIn August 1998, ABC, ESPN and [[ESPN2]] signed a five-year television deal with the NHL, worth a total of approximately US$600 million<ref>{{cite journal|title=Is Disney Goofy To Bid $600 Million For Nhl Tv Rights?|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=Is+Disney+Goofy+To+Bid+%24600+Million+For+Nhl+Tv+Rights%3F+-+08.17.98+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=431349367&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1013552%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|journal=Sports Illustrated|date=August 17, 1998}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal|title=Learning It Cold|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=Learning+It+Cold+-+01.10.00+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=431385002&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1018103%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|author=John Walters|journal=Sports Illustrated|date=January 10, 2000}}</ref> (or $120 million per year). The $120 million per year that ABC and ESPN paid for rights dwarfed the $5.5 million that the NHL received from American national broadcasts in the [[1991\u201392 NHL season|1991\u201392]] season.<ref>{{cite news|title=Best N.H.L. Action Is the Battle Over TV Rights|url=https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9504EFDF103BF934A3575BC0A96E958260&scp=2&sq=NHL+on+ABC&st=nyt|author=Richard Sandomir|date=August 7, 1998|accessdate=March 20, 2008}}</ref> As previously mentioned, as was the case with the [[1992\u201393 NHL season|1992]]&ndash;[[1993\u201394 NHL season|1994]] deal, ABC's subsequent NHL coverage was in reality, made up of time\u2013buys from ESPN. This was noted in copyright beds at the conclusion of the telecasts, i.e. \"The preceding program has been paid for by ESPN, Inc.\" ESPN then signed a similar television rights contract in [[2002\u201303 NBA season|2002]] so it could produce and broadcast [[NBA on ABC|National Basketball Association games on ABC]].\n\n====Regular season====\nThis time around, ABC televised four to five weeks worth of regional games on Saturday afternoons beginning in January. \n\n====Schedules====\n\n=====1999\u20132000=====\n{{Main article|1999\u20132000 NHL season}}<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-srv/sports/nhl/longterm/1999/schedule/nhlsked.htm|work=Washingtonpost.com|title=1999\u20132000 NHL Schedule | date=October 1, 1999}}</ref>\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Date\n! Teams\n! Start times (All times Eastern)\n|'''Commentator crews'''\n|-\n|March 18\n|[[1999\u20132000 Pittsburgh Penguins season|Pittsburgh]] at [[1999\u20132000 Boston Bruins season|Boston]]<br>[[Flyers\u2013Rangers rivalry|New York Rangers at Philadelphia]]<br>[[1999\u20132000 Dallas Stars season|Dallas]] at [[1999\u20132000 Chicago Blackhawks season|Chicago]]<br>[[1999\u20132000 Detroit Red Wings season|Detroit]] at [[1999\u20132000 Colorado Avalanche season|Colorado]]\n|3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.\n|[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Barry Melrose]]<br>[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]<br>[[Dave Strader]] and [[Jim Schoenfeld]]<br>[[Gary Thorne]] and [[Bill Clement]]\n|-\n|March 26\n|[[Flyers\u2013Penguins rivalry|Pittsburgh at Philadelphia]]<br>New York Rangers at Detroit<br>[[Blues\u2013Blackhawks rivalry|St. Louis at Chicago]]<br>Colorado at Dallas\n|1 p.m.<br>1 p.m.<br>1 p.m.<br>1 p.m.\n|[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]<br>[[Dave Strader]] and [[Jim Schoenfeld]]<br>[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Barry Melrose]]<br>[[Gary Thorne]] and [[Bill Clement]]\n|-\n|April 1\n|New York Rangers at Boston<br>[[Flyers\u2013Penguins rivalry|Philadelphia at Pittsburgh]]<br>Detroit at St. Louis<br>[[Freeway Face-Off|Anaheim at Los Angeles]]\n|1 p.m.<br>1 p.m.<br>1 p.m.<br>6 p.m.\n|[[Dave Strader]] and [[Jim Schoenfeld]]<br>[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Barry Melrose]]<br>[[Gary Thorne]] and [[Bill Clement]]<br>[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]\n|-\n|April 9\n|[[Flyers\u2013Rangers rivalry|Philadelphia at New York Rangers]]<br>[[Blues\u2013Blackhawks rivalry|St. Louis at Chicago]]<br>[[1999\u20132000 Phoenix Coyotes season|Phoenix]] at Dallas<br>Detroit at Colorado<br>[[Freeway Face-Off|Los Angeles at Anaheim]]\n|3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.\n|[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]<br>[[Dave Strader]] and [[Jim Schoenfeld]]<br>[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Barry Melrose]]<br>[[Gary Thorne]] and [[Bill Clement]]<br>[[Dave Ryan (sportscaster)|Dave Ryan]] and [[Joe Micheletti]]\n|}\n\n=====2000\u201301=====\n{{main article|2000\u201301 NHL season}}\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Date\n! Teams\n! Start times (All times Eastern)\n|'''Commentator crews'''\n|-\n|March 10 \n|[[Devils\u2013Flyers rivalry|New Jersey at Philadelphia]]<br>[[2000\u201301 Detroit Red Wings season|Detroit]] at [[2000\u201301 St. Louis Blues season|St. Louis]]<br>[[2000\u201301 Colorado Avalanche season|Colorado]] at [[2000\u201301 Dallas Stars season|Dallas]]\n|3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.\n|[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Barry Melrose]]<br>[[Gary Thorne]] and [[Bill Clement]]<br>[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]\n|-\n|March 17\n|[[Flyers-Rangers rivalry|New York Rangers at Philadelphia]]<br>[[Colorado Avalanche\u2013Detroit Red Wings brawl|Detroit at Colorado]]<br>[[Kings\u2013Sharks rivalry|San Jose at Los Angeles]]\n|3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 