as Stars season|Dallas]]<br>[[Islanders\u2013Rangers rivalry|New York Rangers at New York Islanders]]\n|1 p.m.<br>1 p.m.<br>1 p.m.\n|[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]<br>[[Gary Thorne]], [[Bill Clement]], and [[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]<br>[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Brian Engblom]]\n|-\n|February 14 \n|[[Flyers\u2013Rangers rivalry|New York Rangers at Philadelphia]]<br>[[Colorado Avalanche\u2013Detroit Red Wings brawl|Colorado at Detroit]]<br>Boston at [[2003\u201304 Chicago Blackhawks season|Chicago]]\n|3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.\n|[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]<br>[[Gary Thorne]], [[Bill Clement]], and [[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]<br>[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Brian Engblom]]\n|-\n|March 13 \n|Dallas at Detroit<br>[[Devils\u2013Flyers rivalry|New Jersey at Philadelphia]]<br>[[Kings\u2013Sharks rivalry|Los Angeles at San Jose]]\n|3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.\n|[[Gary Thorne]], [[Bill Clement]], and [[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]<br>[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]<br>[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Brian Engblom]]\n|-\n|March 20 \n|[[Flyers\u2013Rangers rivalry|New York Rangers at Philadelphia]]<br>[[2003\u201304 St. Louis Blues season|St. Louis]] at Dallas\n|3 p.m.<br>3 p.m.\n|[[Gary Thorne]], [[Bill Clement]] and [[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]<br>[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]\n|-\n|March 27 \n|[[Colorado Avalanche\u2013Detroit Red Wings brawl|Colorado at Detroit]]<br>[[Flyers\u2013Rangers rivalry|New York Rangers at Philadelphia]]<br>Los Angeles at [[2003\u201304 Calgary Flames season|Calgary]]\n|1:30 p.m.<br>1:30 p.m.<br>6 p.m.\n|[[Gary Thorne]], [[Bill Clement]], and [[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]]<br>[[Steve Levy]] and [[Darren Pang]]<br>[[Mike Emrick]] and [[Brian Engblom]]\n|}\n\n====NHL All-Star Game====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n![[Play-by-play]]\n![[Color commentator]](s)\n!Ice level reporters\n!Studio host\n!Studio analysts\n|-\n|[[2004 National Hockey League All-Star Game|2004]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=2004 NHL All Star Game, Naslund and Bertuzzi Assists (Feb. 8, 2004) (ABC)|id=eL_i8LIxGgs}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=2004 NHL All Star intro from St. Paul - Part 1 of 2 (West)|id=6vbybmkkP6o}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=2004 NHL All Star intro from St. Paul - Part 2 of 2 (East)|id=A0SgtdZMvgc}}</ref>\n|[[Gary Thorne]]\n|[[Bill Clement]] and [[John Davidson (hockey player)|John Davidson]]\n|[[Erin Andrews]] and [[Sam Ryan]]\n|[[John Saunders (journalist)|John Saunders]]\n|[[Barry Melrose]] and [[Darren Pang]] \n|-\n|[[2003 National Hockey League All-Star Game|2003]]\n|[[Gary Thorne]]\n|[[Bill Clement]] and [[John Davidson (hockey player)|John Davidson]]\n|[[Erin Andrews]] and [[Sam Ryan]]\n|[[John Saunders (journalist)|John Saunders]]\n|[[Barry Melrose]] and [[Darren Pang]] \n|-\n|[[2002 National Hockey League All-Star Game|2002]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=NHL on ABC - 2002 NHL All Star Game|id=awPb5GiEG98}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=2002 NHL All Star Game - Player Intros|id=aBzxKQBvQcg}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=2002 NHL All-Star Game, Markus Naslund 2 Goals and 1 Assist (Feb. 2, 2002) (ABC)|id=xx5K2w7uR3g}}</ref><ref>{{YouTube|title=2002 NHL All-Star Game: World 8, North America 5|id=OXoc2ykDfsM}}</ref>\n|[[Gary Thorne]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|[[Brian Engblom]] and [[Darren Pang]]\n|[[John Saunders (journalist)|John Saunders]]\n|[[John Davidson (hockey player)|John Davidson]] and [[Barry Melrose]]\n|-\n|[[2001 National Hockey League All-Star Game|2001]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=2001 NHL All-Star Game: North America 14, World 12|id=wLpjYdvKoDM}}</ref>\n|[[Gary Thorne]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|[[Brian Engblom]] and [[Darren Pang]]\n|[[John Saunders (journalist)|John Saunders]]\n|[[John Davidson (hockey player)|John Davidson]] and [[Barry Melrose]]\n|-\n|[[2000 National Hockey League All-Star Game|2000]]<ref>{{YouTube|title=2000 NHL All-Star Game: World 9, North America 4|id=Iy6cC_NsQ_E}}</ref>\n|[[Gary Thorne]]\n|[[Bill Clement]]\n|[[Brian Engblom]] and [[Darren Pang]]\n|[[John Saunders (journalist)|John Saunders]]\n|[[John Davidson (hockey player)|John Davidson]] and [[Barry Melrose]]\n|}\n\n====Stanley Cup Playoffs 2000\u20132004====\nBesides the [[National Hockey League All-Star Game]]<ref>{{cite journal|title=The NHL|url=http://cnnsi.printthis.clickability.com/pt/cpt?action=cpt&title=The+Nhl+-+02.05.01+-+SI+Vault&expire=&urlID=431385062&fb=Y&url=http%3A%2F%2Fsportsillustrated.cnn.com%2Fvault%2Farticle%2Fmagazine%2FMAG1021673%2F2%2Findex.htm&partnerID=289881|author=Kostya Kennedy|journal=Sports Illustrated|date=February 5, 2001}}</ref>, ABC televised Games 3\u20137 of the Stanley Cup Finals<ref>{{cite journal|title=Under Review|url=http://sportsillustrated.cnn.com/vault/article/magazine/MAG1028974/index.htm|author=Pete McEntegart|work=CNN|date=June 16, 2003}}</ref> in [[prime time]]. In the league's previous broadcast television deal with Fox, the network split coverage of the [[List of Stanley Cup Finals broadcasters|Stanley Cup Finals]] with [[ESPN National Hockey Night|ESPN]]. Games 1, 5 and 7 were usually scheduled to be televised by Fox; Games 2, 3, 4 and 6 by ESPN. However, from [[1995 Stanley Cup Finals|1995]] to [[1998 Stanley Cup Finals|1998]], the Finals were all four-game sweeps; [[1999 Stanley Cup Finals|1999]] ended in six games. The consequence was that \u2013 except for 1995, when Fox did televise Game 4 \u2013 the decisive game was never on network television.\n\n2003 was the only year that ABC broadcast both the [[2003 NBA Finals|NBA]] and the [[2003 Stanley Cup Finals|Stanley Cup Finals]] that involved teams from one city in the same year, as both the [[2002\u201303 New Jersey Nets season|New Jersey Nets]] and the [[2002\u201303 New Jersey Devils season|New Jersey Devils]] were in their respective league's finals. During ABC's broadcast of Game 3 between the [[2002\u201303 San Antonio Spurs season|San Antonio Spurs]] and the Nets in [[New Jersey]] on June 8, [[Brad Nessler]], [[Tom Tolbert]] and [[Bill Walton]] said that ABC was in a unique situation getting ready for both that game and Game 7 of the [[2003 Stanley Cup Finals|Stanley Cup Finals]] between the Devils and the [[2002\u201303 Mighty Ducks of Anaheim season|Mighty Ducks of Anaheim]] the following night, also at [[Continental Airlines Arena]]. [[Gary Thorne]], [[Bill Clement]] and [[John Davidson (ice hockey)|John Davidson]] mentioned this the following night, and thanked Nessler, Tolbert and Walton for promoting ABC's broadcast of Game 7 of the Stanley Cup Finals.<ref>{{cite video|title=NHL on ABC: Game 7 of the 2003 Stanley Cup Finals|medium=television|publisher=ABC Sports|date=June 9, 2003}}</ref>\n\nFollowing the 2003\u201304 season, ESPN was only willing to renew its contract for two additional years at $60 million per year.<ref>{{cite news|title=NHL announces TV deal with NBC|url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/hockey/nhl/2004-05-19-martzke-nbc_x.htm|author=Rudy Martzke|newspaper=USA Today|date=May 19, 2004|accessdate=July 2, 2012}}</ref> ABC refused to televise the Stanley Cup Finals in prime time, suggesting that the Finals games it would telecast be played on weekend afternoons (including a potential Game 7). [[The Walt Disney Company|Disney]] executives later conceded that they overpaid for the 1999\u20132004 deal, so the company's offer to renew the television rights was lower in 2004.<ref>{{cite journal|url=http://www.medialifemagazine.com/news2001/apr01/apr09/4_thurs/news1thursday.html|title=Sports TV get pricier and pricier. Here's why|author=Kevin Downey|journal=Media Life Magazine|date=April 12, 2001|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081013043902/http://www.medialifemagazine.com/news2001/apr01/apr09/4_thurs/news1thursday.html|archivedate=13 October 2008|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n=====Stanley Cup playoffs commentating crews=====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n!Year\n!Round\n!Teams\n!Games\n!Play-by-play\n!Color commentator \n!Ice-level reporter(s)\n|-\n|rowspan=8|[[2000 Stanley Cup